	     <tr><td id="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top"><a id="sj" href="/db/item.html?item=4092&amp;mid=100362837867412">RE: Drop information please</a> <a id="fs8" href="/db/item.html?item=4092&amp;mid=100362837867412#post"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11" /></a>
	     <br clear="all" /><small>Posted @ Sat, Oct 20th 9:39 PM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=61489"><span id="Scholar">Kamlatir, Eater of Souls</span></a><br /><b><span id="Scholar">Scholar</span></b><br /><span id="notbold">66 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.30]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>Hehe, I'm a shadowknight, just stumbled in here by accident. Hello all monks =) The class specific armors in PoG all drop of specific mobs, most often one type of mob drops armor for two classes (sk and cleric armor drops of the same mob I believe). I don't remember which mob drops the monk armor though but that really doesn't matter since you have to clear the other mobs too up there to make any progress. The plane is divided in two parts separated by a river. On the west side of the river drops the smaller pieces of armor, bracers, boots and such. This side needs to be cleared before crossing over to the east side. The named ones are mostly on the east side and they seem to have the best chance of dropping chest and leg pieces. Some of the named ones summon a specific type of mobs which explains why the west side needs to be cleared before attempting them. Another thing, the drop rates in this plane is nothing like the ones in for example Hate. In Hate every third mob drops something (on the first floor, not the second) but in PoG the drop rate is awful. In one night only 2 sk pieces dropped.</p>&nbsp;<br /></td></tr>
